The paper proposes an unsupervised image segmentation algorithm that uses a discriminative classifier trained on color and texture information obtained from each superpixel. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of regularization techniques and Markov random fields suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of superpixels and texture information also suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm on a standard dataset suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
